  "name": "Horn of the Sun Aurochs",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>A horn of the sun aurochs grants a +2 item bonus to Performance checks when played as an instrument.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> Interact <span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span></p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The horn is clearly audible for hundreds of feet, but within a @Template[type:emanation|distance:20], the sound causes agony in those who wish harm upon the user; the horn also sheds bright light in that area and dim light to the next 20 feet. Enemies of the user in this area take @Damage[7d6[sonic]] damage and @Damage[7d6[spirit]] damage (@Check[type:fortitude|dc:30|basic:true] save). Creatures that are specifically vulnerable to sunlight are also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 1} if they fail this save or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened 2} on a critical failure. This activation also attempts to counteract any darkness or sleep effects in the area ([[/r 1d20+23 #Counteract]]{+23} counteract check).</p>"
